Startup U have to import particular modules Flask redirect url_for Baisici startup syntax app = Flask (__name__) @app.route(&#34;/&#34;) def home (): return &#34;This is the Main Page &#34; if __name__ == &#34;__main__&#34;: app.run() Every page is defined by the function @app.route(&#34;/admin&#34;) def admin (): return &#34;This is the Admin Page&#34; To make sthings easier use duble slaches Example /about/ Redirect The simples is use redirect method @app.route(&#34;/admin&#34;) def admin (): return redirect(url_for(&#34;home&#34;)) This will redirect a person from admin to home
Theres also an optionm to redirect someone to the commucniate @app.route(&#34;/&lt;name&gt;&#34;) def about (name): return f&#34;Hello {name}! This will print the varaible inserted into search u only has to put in html format
Python code in html This allows us to write semi native python code To refrence smth use **{{name of variable {% for i in range (10) %} p&gt; Hello &lt;p {% endfor %} # This treats it as variable {% {x} %} {%if x !=2 %} {%endif %} Template Inharientence U can inheraite tampletes by code blox u just use { % block name %} {% endblock %} To extend the template u just use {% extends &ldquo;base.html&rdquo; %} &lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt; &lt;html lang=&#34;en&#34;&gt; &lt;head&gt; &lt;meta charset=&#34;UTF-8&#34;&gt; &lt;meta http-equiv=&#34;X-UA-Compatible&#34; content=&#34;IE=edge&#34;&gt; &lt;meta name=&#34;viewport&#34; content=&#34;width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0&#34;&gt; &lt;title&gt;{% block title %} {% endblock %}&lt;/title&gt; &lt;/head&gt; &lt;body&gt; {% block content %} {% endblock %} &lt;/body&gt; &lt;/html&gt; JS and Css Java script and css file should be located in a static folder and linked by the url similarly to the icons {{ url_for(&lsquo;static&rsquo;, filename=&lsquo;css/box.css&rsquo;) }}

